Sydney Devine  (11 January 1940 – 13 February 2021) was a Scottish singer.
Devine was born in Bellside, a settlement near the village of Cleland, North Lanarkshire, Scotland, in January 1940.

In 2003, Devine became a Member of the Order of the British Empire (MBE) for services to music.
In September 2017, Devine, at the age of 77, announced a nationwide tour with his daughter, Debby McGregor, Scotland’s leading female ventriloquist, nearly 20 years since his previous tour.
